WEBVTT

00:56.931 --> 00:58.892
I won't expect anything from you,

00:58.975 --> 01:00.060
EPISODE 5

01:00.143 --> 01:02.020
...so just let me see you.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.482
I promise I won't get caught.

01:09.027 --> 01:10.153
No, that's not right.

01:11.446 --> 01:12.947
I understand how you feel, but--

01:13.198 --> 01:14.282
I'm talking about you.

01:17.202 --> 01:18.828
I won't get caught by you.

01:26.628 --> 01:27.670
I told you.

01:29.005 --> 01:30.924
I went there because I wanted to see you.

01:33.676 --> 01:36.054
I went there impulsively
because I wanted to see you,

01:38.515 --> 01:40.058
but the moment I saw Gi-seok...

01:43.186 --> 01:46.523
I felt as if someone was telling me
that I was doing what I shouldn't do.

01:48.399 --> 01:49.442
So?

01:51.069 --> 01:52.779
You're not going to get caught by me

01:54.697 --> 01:56.032
and watch me secretly?

01:57.242 --> 01:58.576
If you allow me to do so.

01:59.911 --> 02:02.288
- If you say that I can't--
- Of course you can't.

02:03.540 --> 02:04.582
I can't allow that.

02:13.883 --> 02:16.302
Right. From your perspective,
it is complete nonsense.

02:16.427 --> 02:17.679
What is my perspective?

02:20.348 --> 02:22.684
If you know
that someone is watching you secretly--

02:22.767 --> 02:23.768
Who cares?

02:25.395 --> 02:26.771
You said you won't get caught.

02:28.731 --> 02:31.151
Then I wouldn't be aware of it,
so it doesn't matter.

02:35.655 --> 02:36.781
The problem is me.

02:38.575 --> 02:39.576
Yes.

02:40.910 --> 02:43.246
You can see me whenever you want.

02:47.500 --> 02:48.751
But what should I do, then?

02:55.633 --> 02:59.512
Shall I also get your permission
to peep at you secretly?

03:03.308 --> 03:05.185
Why are you only thinking about yourself?

03:05.268 --> 03:07.103
Is your satisfaction all that matters?

03:08.396 --> 03:10.231
Don't you care about how I'd feel?

03:12.650 --> 03:14.569
Were you always this selfish?

03:19.240 --> 03:20.992
Shall I really let myself be selfish?

03:26.748 --> 03:27.749
No.

04:36.901 --> 04:39.654
MY GIRL

05:44.052 --> 05:45.178
We should end this here.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.100
I thought about it on our way here.

05:53.436 --> 05:54.520
If we keep this up,

05:54.687 --> 05:57.315
you'll lose many things
because of your fleeting emotions.

05:59.108 --> 06:01.110
And a lot more pain will follow.

06:02.945 --> 06:05.198
I'm not saying this
to look like a good person.

06:05.448 --> 06:06.616
I was being selfish.

06:13.706 --> 06:14.999
To be more honest with you,

06:19.045 --> 06:22.340
I was wallowing in emotions
that I thought I'd never feel again.

06:24.592 --> 06:25.676
I was being reckless.

06:26.594 --> 06:28.971
I keep getting lame, pathetic thoughts.

06:31.641 --> 06:34.102
If this continues,
I'll turn into a total loser.

06:37.522 --> 06:38.564
In any case,

06:39.774 --> 06:41.567
what am I supposed to do, then?

06:42.902 --> 06:44.529
I don't know. This is killing me.

06:46.489 --> 06:48.908
Do you actually think I'll buy that lie?

06:53.663 --> 06:55.123
Just act like you believe me.

06:57.375 --> 06:58.584
I'm begging you.

07:00.711 --> 07:01.838
Help me.

07:27.655 --> 07:29.574
They'll get married eventually, you know.

07:30.199 --> 07:32.201
They might waste another year
at this rate,

07:32.493 --> 07:35.413
so all I'm saying is
we should probably pressure them a little.

07:37.999 --> 07:39.584
That's not how I'd describe it.

07:40.293 --> 07:43.754
It's more like, "I'm the only adult
in this family, so you all must obey me."

07:44.380 --> 07:46.090
Don't you know how Jeong-in is?

07:48.301 --> 07:51.095
Because she was uncomfortable
that you taught at her school,

07:51.220 --> 07:52.472
she went on a hunger strike

07:52.555 --> 07:54.474
and managed to transfer to another school.

07:54.640 --> 07:56.684
When she feels
she's right about something,

07:56.934 --> 07:59.103
she has to see it through no matter what.

07:59.812 --> 08:02.815
I mean, why do you think
Seo-in made such an alarming comment?

08:04.734 --> 08:07.820
Do something if you think
you understand the girls that well.

08:08.362 --> 08:10.364
You're doing nothing
like a mere spectator.

08:10.448 --> 08:12.617
That's why the girls think
that I'm overbearing.

08:13.284 --> 08:14.952
You are overbearing though.

08:17.079 --> 08:18.539
So what? Just see what happens?

08:21.000 --> 08:23.085
I'm sure Jeong-in has a plan.

08:23.169 --> 08:25.087
She has a strong sense of responsibility.

08:35.973 --> 08:39.477
I'll meet up with her and try to find out
what's going on.

08:49.820 --> 08:53.115
I'm off. I'll get going, then.

08:56.494 --> 08:57.578
Hello.

08:58.412 --> 09:00.498
- Mom.
- Hey, wait up!

09:00.915 --> 09:02.875
My gosh. It's been a while, Jeong-in.

09:02.959 --> 09:04.001
Yes, hello.

09:06.295 --> 09:08.756
- We'll get going, then.
- All right.

09:09.840 --> 09:11.509
- See you next time.
- Okay, take care.

09:11.592 --> 09:12.593
Bye.

09:13.928 --> 09:15.263
Do you want to go for lunch?

09:16.556 --> 09:18.140
Why would I have lunch with you?

09:20.226 --> 09:21.060
Mom.

09:24.063 --> 09:25.064
Just a second.

09:43.958 --> 09:45.501
- Show me what you did today.
- Gosh.

09:47.461 --> 09:48.504
Mom, please.

09:50.256 --> 09:52.341
Do you respect me as your mom?

09:52.883 --> 09:55.136
How could you keep it even from me?

09:55.553 --> 09:57.054
If I didn't see Jae-in that day,

09:58.306 --> 09:59.599
you'd still be hiding it.

10:00.474 --> 10:01.892
No, I wouldn't.

10:02.393 --> 10:04.353
First off,
I was surprised to see her back.

10:04.562 --> 10:06.314
And I've been all over the place.

10:07.106 --> 10:08.399
With what?

10:08.691 --> 10:10.318
You have the same job.

10:10.401 --> 10:13.112
And you threatened us not to bring up
the topic of marriage.

10:13.195 --> 10:14.530
What's been keeping you busy?

10:14.697 --> 10:16.866
Jeez, when did I threaten you?

10:17.325 --> 10:19.201
You also agree that Dad was out of line.

10:19.410 --> 10:21.662
Look at you getting all riled up
with no remorse.

10:23.539 --> 10:24.540
I'm sorry.

10:26.334 --> 10:29.420
As for the thing with Jae-in,
I'll talk to Dad about it.

10:31.339 --> 10:32.882
She's not the only problem.

10:34.008 --> 10:36.260
Seo-in came over the other day
and threw a fit.

10:37.595 --> 10:39.680
She did? What did she say?

10:42.099 --> 10:43.225
What do you mean?

10:43.934 --> 10:45.645
Do you know something that I don't?

10:46.812 --> 10:50.358
No, it's just that it's out of character
for Seo-in to do such a thing.

10:51.734 --> 10:52.818
Well...

10:52.943 --> 10:55.821
I don't know what's gotten into Si-hoon,
but he also stopped by

10:56.030 --> 10:59.492
and went on about how we should
encourage you to get married soon.

11:00.493 --> 11:01.535
And what happened?

11:02.286 --> 11:03.788
What do you think?

11:04.705 --> 11:08.209
Seo-in told your dad
not to make you end up like her.

11:17.009 --> 11:19.053
- Mom.
- Yes?

11:20.596 --> 11:23.391
What kind of guy should I marry?

11:25.434 --> 11:26.602
What about Gi-seok?

11:27.436 --> 11:28.854
You don't think it'll work out?

11:32.983 --> 11:35.403
Arguing and fighting
can make you get more attached.

11:36.070 --> 11:37.738
It's not easy to sever such a bond.

11:40.491 --> 11:41.992
I didn't say we're breaking up.

11:50.418 --> 11:52.878
You can't control what your heart wants.

11:55.131 --> 11:57.466
This has been done too many times.

11:57.550 --> 12:00.886
- What about this one? It's simple.
- It looks like a copy of the other one.

12:00.970 --> 12:03.723
- Gosh, I'm getting a headache.
- Maybe this...

12:10.521 --> 12:11.981
Forget a special theme.

12:12.690 --> 12:15.735
For example,
"Book of the Year on My Bookshelf."

12:15.860 --> 12:17.194
How about such an easy one?

12:17.278 --> 12:19.405
Yes, I like how simple it is.
What do you think?

12:20.114 --> 12:22.533
"Unexpectedly You"?

12:23.784 --> 12:25.035
What?

12:26.162 --> 12:27.163
I mean...

12:27.580 --> 12:29.623
Who are you referring to?

12:30.207 --> 12:33.544
Well, no one specific.

12:34.670 --> 12:37.298
It's still the seasonal theme,
but I added another element.

12:38.424 --> 12:42.178
We usually get the same participants
for this book review event, you know.

12:43.220 --> 12:46.223
But when people see the phrase,
"Unexpectedly You,"

12:47.391 --> 12:49.477
even those who have never done it
might think,

12:49.602 --> 12:51.645
"Can someone like me
participate in it too?"

12:51.729 --> 12:54.398
I think it can be motivating.

12:56.692 --> 12:57.777
Not a good idea, right?

12:58.861 --> 13:00.571
Then let's scratch this off the list.

13:00.780 --> 13:01.989
I love that idea.

13:03.824 --> 13:05.701
Finally, we have our theme!

13:07.119 --> 13:08.204
It's awesome.

13:09.163 --> 13:11.207
- Jeong-in, you rock.
- Does it sound okay?

13:11.290 --> 13:12.875
- Yes.
- It's amazing.

13:13.334 --> 13:14.418
It's pretty good.

13:16.420 --> 13:20.090
And just one more box
of amlodipine, please.

13:21.759 --> 13:24.345
Oh, internal medicine doctors
won't prescribe it anymore,

13:24.428 --> 13:26.096
so you can take it out of our order.

13:27.348 --> 13:28.349
Yes.

13:29.433 --> 13:30.476
Okay, thank you.

13:41.195 --> 13:42.738
You know it's a rare opportunity.

13:45.324 --> 13:46.534
Yes, I'm fully aware.

13:46.992 --> 13:48.911
And that's why I thought long and hard.

13:48.994 --> 13:51.288
Then how could your answer be no?

13:52.248 --> 13:53.290
I'm sorry.

13:53.874 --> 13:55.084
I don't need your apology.

13:56.168 --> 13:58.045
Don't say you can't handle the pressure

13:58.128 --> 14:00.923
because neither the higher-ups
nor I will buy such an excuse.

14:01.924 --> 14:04.301
What is it? You must have another reason.

14:09.807 --> 14:11.392
I bet you got a job offer.

14:11.809 --> 14:13.769
No, that's not the case at all.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.396
That's what everyone says.

14:15.479 --> 14:18.357
Everyone acts all surprised like that
and ends up quitting.

14:19.608 --> 14:21.902
If that's what you want to believe,
then go ahead.

14:23.571 --> 14:26.240
If that's not the reason,
then why are you being like this?

14:30.077 --> 14:32.997
I have nothing to say to you. I'm sorry.

14:35.082 --> 14:36.375
You're driving me nuts.

14:37.835 --> 14:39.670
The entire building consists of clinics,

14:39.753 --> 14:41.297
so you'll get new patients easily.

14:41.380 --> 14:43.507
Transportation-wise,
a subway station is nearby.

14:44.174 --> 14:47.595
This clinic's owner wouldn't be moving out
if he didn't have health issues.

14:48.512 --> 14:50.890
Does Dr. Sin own all the equipment
and machines here?

14:51.056 --> 14:54.184
Of course. We set everything up for him,
including the decor.

14:55.144 --> 14:56.395
So when can I take it?

14:58.355 --> 14:59.648
You'll actually take it?

15:05.779 --> 15:08.282
Call me right after you speak
with the building owner.

15:08.365 --> 15:09.575
I'll sign the lease.

15:10.284 --> 15:11.744
But this building is new,

15:11.827 --> 15:14.872
so the deposit and rent are
on the higher side. Have I mentioned it?

15:14.955 --> 15:16.582
That doesn't matter at all.

15:16.665 --> 15:19.418
I just want a lot of discount
on the equipment and machines.

15:20.002 --> 15:23.422
Sounds good. I've been doing business
with him for years, so it'll go well.

15:24.882 --> 15:28.594
Then when can you have
the fees and deposit ready?

15:28.677 --> 15:30.596
First, do your best with the negotiation.

15:31.889 --> 15:32.932
Okay, I will.

15:35.601 --> 15:38.270
Do you think I'm biting this
when I can't even afford it?

15:38.354 --> 15:40.606
- No, that's not what I meant. I was just--
- Then?

15:40.773 --> 15:43.275
- See what you can do.
- All right, I will.

15:45.778 --> 15:47.363
- Thank you.
- Get going.

15:47.446 --> 15:49.073
- Okay, I'll be in touch.
- All right.

15:54.328 --> 15:57.206
Jeez, everyone is getting on my nerves.

16:08.926 --> 16:10.260
Did you see Si-hoon recently?

16:11.845 --> 16:12.930
Yes, we met up.

16:15.224 --> 16:16.892
He said he needs to take out a loan.

16:17.267 --> 16:18.686
He wants to expand his clinic.

16:24.108 --> 16:25.567
He said we should all hang out.

16:27.778 --> 16:28.904
When would be good?

16:29.947 --> 16:30.864
Forget it.

16:32.449 --> 16:33.617
Forget what?

16:35.202 --> 16:36.453
Why hang out with him?

16:36.912 --> 16:39.623
Give him some excuse about the loan
and don't get involved.

16:43.335 --> 16:44.294
What is your reason?

16:46.422 --> 16:47.548
Just because.

16:48.424 --> 16:49.591
Why get involved?

16:50.801 --> 16:53.345
He said he'll actively support
our plan to get married.

16:58.183 --> 16:59.268
What's with that stare?

17:01.770 --> 17:03.522
You really don't want to get married?

17:14.491 --> 17:16.076
What do your parents say about it?

17:19.705 --> 17:21.248
If that's sorted out,

17:21.874 --> 17:23.167
you'll do it no matter what?

17:24.418 --> 17:26.295
It's not something to be stubborn about.

17:26.587 --> 17:28.255
You just don't want to lose, do you?

17:29.631 --> 17:31.592
It's not like you let me win every time.

17:31.675 --> 17:34.178
- Gi-seok.
- Forget it. Let's change the topic.

17:39.099 --> 17:41.685
This is why I'm scared
to spend time with you these days.

17:42.686 --> 17:44.146
We always end up arguing.

17:44.229 --> 17:47.066
We keep fighting, and I end up
blaming it all on my bad temper.

17:47.941 --> 17:49.777
I don't even know what to do anymore.

17:56.492 --> 17:57.576
Get in.

18:06.210 --> 18:07.711
What do you want?

18:09.213 --> 18:10.464
What do you want me to do?

18:13.509 --> 18:14.635
Nothing. Let's just go.

18:15.719 --> 18:18.305
We won't get married, okay?

18:20.557 --> 18:21.767
Isn't that what you want?

18:22.559 --> 18:24.019
I won't bring it up. Happy now?

18:26.939 --> 18:29.233
- For God's sake.
- Happy about what?

18:31.318 --> 18:33.153
Do you think I'm an idiot

18:33.779 --> 18:35.280
because I haven't brought it up?

18:36.907 --> 18:38.742
Do you really think I wouldn't know

18:39.243 --> 18:40.828
what your parents think about me?

18:42.746 --> 18:44.832
Do you even know what it feels like

18:45.415 --> 18:47.126
to be disapproved of?

18:48.544 --> 18:51.088
How could I be excited,
fully knowing they don't like me?

18:51.797 --> 18:53.215
Do you think I'm crazy or what?

18:53.507 --> 18:54.800
Would you be excited?

18:57.261 --> 18:59.263
- Jeong-in, that's--
- I haven't brought it up

19:00.264 --> 19:02.141
because I knew I'd feel petty and lame.

19:02.850 --> 19:06.061
Did you have to make me talk about it
and feel this miserable?

19:06.353 --> 19:07.938
Why are you being so mean?

19:08.605 --> 19:10.524
And you say you want to marry me?

19:10.899 --> 19:12.526
Do you actually mean it?

19:13.652 --> 19:15.112
Even just for a moment...

19:20.701 --> 19:22.828
Have you ever felt sorry for me?

19:26.373 --> 19:28.417
I never begged for your love

19:28.667 --> 19:30.335
or pestered you to marry me.

19:31.086 --> 19:33.463
I just hoped you'd understand how I feel.

19:33.881 --> 19:35.382
Is it that hard?

19:36.884 --> 19:38.010
Okay, I heard you.

19:39.887 --> 19:41.847
- Now, I know.
- No.

19:43.974 --> 19:45.350
You've known from the get-go.

19:46.852 --> 19:49.062
You've been just neglecting it all along.

19:50.355 --> 19:52.357
That's what hurts me the most.

22:13.248 --> 22:15.292
- Hello.
- You're early.

22:20.964 --> 22:22.049
Hello.

22:22.132 --> 22:23.967
Do you have any medicine for hangovers?

22:25.552 --> 22:27.346
Do you have any medicine for hangovers?

22:29.181 --> 22:30.390
I need something strong.

22:30.474 --> 22:31.975
Medicine for hangovers?

22:42.110 --> 22:43.904
- Here you go.
- How much is it?

22:47.074 --> 22:48.116
It's 4,000 won.

23:19.689 --> 23:20.774
You're here.

23:22.067 --> 23:23.235
This is for Eun-u.

23:23.402 --> 23:24.986
They're my son's shoes and clothes.

23:25.195 --> 23:27.531
They're barely worn,
and some of them are brand new.

23:27.906 --> 23:28.949
Thank you.

23:31.743 --> 23:34.371
Does the lady you're seeing
know about Eun-u?

23:35.539 --> 23:36.998
I'm not seeing anyone.

23:37.624 --> 23:39.584
You can't fool me.

23:39.668 --> 23:41.336
I'm not fooling you.

23:43.046 --> 23:45.674
It looked like you were seeing someone.
Is it over already?

23:48.718 --> 23:49.678
I'm too good for her.

23:50.303 --> 23:52.222
Get out. Get out of here.

23:52.347 --> 23:53.348
Get out already.

23:54.182 --> 23:55.267
Give me that.

23:59.438 --> 24:01.523
Things like this.
"Budget for book purchases."

24:01.773 --> 24:04.734
The students don't even have time
to read their textbooks.

24:06.570 --> 24:09.531
And this too, "the reserve fund."
Take out things like this first.

24:13.702 --> 24:14.786
Here.

24:21.042 --> 24:23.545
The budget is almost finalized,

24:24.045 --> 24:26.089
but I asked him to take out
a few more things.

24:30.177 --> 24:33.430
You must be sad about retiring soon.

24:35.348 --> 24:38.852
You're expected to retire so early.
You can definitely work a few more years.

24:42.189 --> 24:45.942
Well,
I've worked in education my whole life.

24:46.818 --> 24:49.738
But I can't say it's been rewarding.
I guess I have more regrets.

24:52.282 --> 24:55.076
Does your second daughter
still work at the library?

24:56.411 --> 24:58.497
Yes, what she does
is related to her major.

25:01.041 --> 25:02.167
What is she good at?

25:03.084 --> 25:05.086
- Pardon?
- Your daughter.

25:05.545 --> 25:07.088
She must be good at something.

25:10.967 --> 25:12.177
You see,

25:13.386 --> 25:16.473
I know that she's my daughter,
but she's exceptional in many aspects.

25:17.474 --> 25:20.352
She's smart,
and she has her own opinions about things.

25:20.644 --> 25:22.771
- I mean, she is...
- Who does she take after?

25:24.940 --> 25:26.316
Me, of course.

25:31.530 --> 25:34.991
My wife is an upright person,

25:35.992 --> 25:38.703
and Jeong-in is just like her.

25:39.287 --> 25:40.205
That's good.

25:41.414 --> 25:42.374
Yes.

25:43.625 --> 25:45.335
Why are you asking about her though?

25:46.628 --> 25:48.547
I was just curious as to what she's like.

25:51.174 --> 25:52.384
Let's go for lunch.

25:55.637 --> 25:56.680
Hey.

25:57.264 --> 25:59.307
Are you not going to get married?

26:00.475 --> 26:02.519
All you do is play sports
with your buddies.

26:03.520 --> 26:05.146
Don't laugh.

26:07.357 --> 26:09.859
Hey, that will make
even the most loyal woman run away.

26:12.946 --> 26:14.698
Get your act together already.

26:18.326 --> 26:20.996
I'll check the school schedule
and let you know.

26:22.205 --> 26:23.248
All right.

26:28.628 --> 26:32.090
It sounds like Gi-seok wants to use
the basketball court again this weekend.

26:32.173 --> 26:35.135
Sure, I'll ask the admin office staff
about it.

26:37.178 --> 26:38.680
Like I mentioned earlier,

26:39.306 --> 26:41.433
Jeong-in always acts on her beliefs,

26:42.142 --> 26:45.103
and she's incredibly
thoughtful and upright.

26:46.146 --> 26:50.442
In other words,
she'll never betray anyone.

26:52.444 --> 26:55.280
I know that she's your daughter,
but don't trust her too much.

26:56.406 --> 26:58.283
How do you think I've come this far?

26:59.242 --> 27:01.870
Even if it's my child,
I don't believe everything I hear.

27:02.203 --> 27:05.081
The same goes for you.
I don't believe everything you're saying

27:05.957 --> 27:07.292
about your daughter.

27:08.752 --> 27:11.338
How dare I tell you
things that aren't true?

27:11.755 --> 27:13.048
I'd never do that.

27:13.673 --> 27:16.926
And she's my daughter, for God's sake.
That's just absurd.

27:17.218 --> 27:19.471
Honestly,
I'd rather tell her not to get married.

27:19.554 --> 27:21.389
I'd just never do something like that.

27:22.557 --> 27:25.226
You see,
Jeong-in may not be the greatest catch,

27:25.310 --> 27:27.187
but she doesn't lack anything.

27:29.314 --> 27:30.523
All right. Eat your food.

27:43.662 --> 27:45.246
I'm going to break up with Gi-seok.

27:47.457 --> 27:49.250
Do you like the pharmacist that much?

27:49.959 --> 27:51.961
Enough to end your relationship?

27:53.588 --> 27:54.964
That's not the only reason.

27:56.216 --> 27:57.550
I guess you won't believe me.

27:59.344 --> 28:02.138
I do believe you as I wasn't
in support of your relationship.

28:04.766 --> 28:07.894
But you're basically saying
you've decided to betray your boyfriend.

28:09.521 --> 28:11.231
It's just bad timing, that's all.

28:11.856 --> 28:13.650
Call it unfair, but that is betrayal.

28:16.528 --> 28:17.862
Should I stay with him, then?

28:19.489 --> 28:21.157
Gosh.

28:21.616 --> 28:24.452
If you can be with him
when you have feelings for another man.

28:30.959 --> 28:32.293
You can't break up with him.

28:33.211 --> 28:36.548
I mean, it's not that you can't do it.
Your boyfriend won't let you go.

28:38.591 --> 28:40.719
He can't swallow his pride,
so he won't do that.

28:41.428 --> 28:42.721
Then what if you get caught?

28:43.805 --> 28:47.016
What will happen if that proud man
finds out that another guy beat him?

28:47.434 --> 28:48.893
Do you think he'll let you go?

28:50.520 --> 28:53.314
And this guy isn't a stranger.
They went to college together.

28:53.690 --> 28:55.275
He won't let you go, 100 percent.

28:59.320 --> 29:02.574
How could my ex and I go cold turkey
after being together for six years?

29:02.991 --> 29:04.868
Because there was no one else involved.

29:04.951 --> 29:07.245
If there was a third party involved,

29:07.787 --> 29:09.873
the war would be still going on.

29:12.834 --> 29:15.462
Whatever, I don't care.
I can't be with him anymore.

29:17.881 --> 29:20.341
Well, is the pharmacist
just waiting for you or what?

29:24.220 --> 29:25.430
I can't

29:27.098 --> 29:28.183
be with him either.

29:31.269 --> 29:34.147
So you won't date him
even if you break up with your boyfriend?

29:36.441 --> 29:37.650
I'm not sure

29:39.611 --> 29:41.112
if I can stay by his side.

29:44.741 --> 29:46.868
Hold on. I'm not following at all.

29:48.161 --> 29:49.204
What?

29:52.916 --> 29:54.000
I'll explain later.

29:56.211 --> 29:57.504
Gosh, my hands are shaking.

29:59.672 --> 30:01.966
- When can I pick them up?
- The day after tomorrow.

30:02.091 --> 30:04.219
I'll drop them off on the way
to buy something.

30:04.302 --> 30:05.470
- Thank you.
- No problem.

30:05.553 --> 30:07.096
- Have a nice day.
- You too. Bye.

30:10.642 --> 30:12.936
- What do you think?
- Sorry? About what?

30:13.937 --> 30:15.313
The owner of the corner store.

30:16.105 --> 30:18.650
That's her daughter who got divorced
about two years ago

30:18.733 --> 30:21.361
and recently moved into her place
with a kid.

30:22.403 --> 30:23.446
For Ji-ho?

30:23.530 --> 30:26.533
Obviously. Why else would I bring it up?

30:27.492 --> 30:28.618
Just leave him be.

30:29.619 --> 30:31.120
- He'll find someone.
- Goodness.

30:31.955 --> 30:33.790
He'll grow old all alone at this rate.

30:34.040 --> 30:35.583
I don't want to be like this,

30:36.459 --> 30:40.421
but I feel like Ji-ho is wasting
all his time.

30:44.050 --> 30:46.511
What about Eun-u's mom?
No news from her whatsoever?

30:50.557 --> 30:53.309
Do you want to see Ji-ho
going all crazy again?

30:54.769 --> 30:55.895
Don't even bring her up.

31:00.775 --> 31:01.985
My pumpkin is here.

31:02.944 --> 31:04.028
Eun-u.

31:04.571 --> 31:06.698
Hello. Hui-seong and Eun-u, right?

31:07.156 --> 31:08.908
Hui-seong, your mom is here.

31:08.992 --> 31:11.828
Let's bow. Bye.

31:12.287 --> 31:13.830
Eun-u, your grandmother is here.

31:15.248 --> 31:17.625
He ate all his food and had fun today.

31:18.751 --> 31:19.961
Eun-u, let's bow.

31:20.044 --> 31:21.963
- Bye.
- Bye.

31:22.964 --> 31:25.758
- I'll see you tomorrow. Take care.
- Yes, thank you.

31:29.679 --> 31:32.265
Did you have fun with your friends?

31:33.558 --> 31:35.018
- Grandma.
- Yes?

31:36.060 --> 31:38.646
- When is Daddy coming home?
- Why do you ask?

31:40.023 --> 31:40.940
The library.

31:41.524 --> 31:42.442
What?

31:43.109 --> 31:45.153
What is at that library?

31:45.445 --> 31:48.031
The library I took you to
is just like that place.

31:48.114 --> 31:49.991
No, it's different.

31:50.074 --> 31:52.702
You keep saying that,
but I don't know how it's different.

31:53.494 --> 31:55.747
Was there something special
at the other library?

31:58.625 --> 32:01.294
I can't take you there unless you tell me.

32:02.003 --> 32:02.921
The teacher.

32:04.088 --> 32:05.131
"Teacher"?

32:06.174 --> 32:07.926
There was a teacher at the library?

32:08.301 --> 32:09.469
Yes.

32:10.511 --> 32:12.639
- Does Daddy know the teacher?
- Yes.

32:12.722 --> 32:14.933
- How do they know each other?
- I don't know.

32:26.152 --> 32:29.489
Those who suck always invest
in state-of-the-art equipment.

32:29.948 --> 32:32.450
How many times must I tell you?
You're no match for me.

32:33.201 --> 32:36.454
Hey, let's say you got better grades
and everything else.

32:36.996 --> 32:38.873
But I'm better when it comes to dating.

32:38.957 --> 32:39.958
Do you admit it?

32:40.041 --> 32:42.168
You just hit on girls.
That's not called dating.

32:42.251 --> 32:44.629
Hey, when you were dating that girl
back then...

32:49.050 --> 32:49.884
I'm sorry.

32:55.223 --> 32:56.933
Every time I eat this fried chicken,

32:58.393 --> 32:59.978
I'm impressed by how good it is.

33:02.730 --> 33:07.068
If I invested in something like this
years ago and made money off it,

33:07.151 --> 33:09.821
I'd probably be cruising
around the world now.

33:11.656 --> 33:13.574
How did you even land a job at a bank?

33:14.867 --> 33:18.454
Hey, I'm everyone's favorite at work.

33:19.247 --> 33:20.999
The manager is so fond of me as well.

33:21.624 --> 33:22.667
Gi-seok.

33:27.130 --> 33:28.131
Hey.

33:28.965 --> 33:30.341
His girlfriend is so pretty.

33:31.634 --> 33:33.594
He keeps saying they're getting married,

33:36.639 --> 33:38.391
but I don't really think he wants to.

33:39.726 --> 33:40.560
Why not?

33:40.643 --> 33:43.187
They've been together for a long time,
you know.

33:43.604 --> 33:44.564
That's probably why.

33:44.647 --> 33:46.357
Are all long-term couples like that?

33:47.066 --> 33:48.568
Then why are they still together?

33:48.818 --> 33:50.361
And what does that make her?

33:52.113 --> 33:53.489
Why are you getting mad at me?

34:05.501 --> 34:06.502
About Yeong-jae...

34:07.670 --> 34:09.047
He must be studying very hard.

34:09.881 --> 34:11.090
I can't get a hold of him.

34:11.883 --> 34:13.551
Leave him alone. Don't distract him.

34:14.135 --> 34:15.219
So...

34:16.512 --> 34:17.680
what's your plan?

34:19.015 --> 34:20.850
I mean, you can't stay jobless forever.

34:22.727 --> 34:25.563
Don't underestimate me.
There are so many things that I can do.

34:27.774 --> 34:29.567
I can get many part-time jobs as well.

34:32.612 --> 34:34.197
I'm good enough to teach piano.

34:35.364 --> 34:37.950
Painting and French too.

34:39.035 --> 34:40.703
And I can converse in English.

34:43.247 --> 34:45.291
When did you learn all those things?

34:47.168 --> 34:49.212
While you were failing
the civil service exam.

34:51.839 --> 34:54.342
Hello, welcome to Language Excursion.
I'm Lee Seo-in.

34:54.801 --> 34:58.054
The Ministry of Employment and Labor
recently released...

34:58.137 --> 34:59.347
What do you think of her?

35:00.807 --> 35:03.392
I'm a huge fan of hers.
She's very close to my ideal type.

35:05.144 --> 35:07.146
Do you like girls who act all coy?

35:08.231 --> 35:10.274
What? She's a news anchor.

35:10.358 --> 35:12.610
- I know.
- Right.

35:13.402 --> 35:15.029
"Coy" is not the right word at all.

35:15.279 --> 35:18.241
I think she's sophisticated and elegant.

35:18.324 --> 35:19.325
"Elegant"?

35:19.909 --> 35:21.244
Elegant, my ass.

35:22.578 --> 35:23.830
What's our total?

35:24.831 --> 35:25.873
Why?

35:26.958 --> 35:28.042
Hey.

35:28.793 --> 35:30.253
Hey, who's texting you?

35:31.295 --> 35:32.421
It's Hyeon-su.

35:33.297 --> 35:34.799
He's out drinking with Ji-ho now.

35:35.758 --> 35:38.177
Let's join them. Let's go!

35:38.886 --> 35:40.012
It'll be awkward.

35:40.179 --> 35:43.057
If they see us, they'll be like,
"Look at you two!"

35:43.141 --> 35:44.475
They'll get the wrong idea.

35:44.642 --> 35:46.727
Gosh, they won't. We're just friends.

35:47.186 --> 35:50.106
And I'll just tell them
that I came to see the pharmacist.

35:50.815 --> 35:54.819
Hey, are you actually interested in Ji-ho?

35:55.319 --> 35:56.946
You keep asking about him.

35:57.822 --> 35:59.407
Why? Are you jealous?

36:00.074 --> 36:01.367
Hey.

36:02.285 --> 36:03.744
Nonsense. Cut it out.

36:05.163 --> 36:09.125
Well, don't pull funny pranks on Ji-ho.

36:10.960 --> 36:11.794
Why not?

36:13.588 --> 36:14.797
No reason.

36:16.048 --> 36:17.592
- Is he seeing someone?
- Yes.

36:17.842 --> 36:18.926
Well, no.

36:20.595 --> 36:23.264
There's someone he likes. A lot, actually.

36:23.931 --> 36:26.767
- Who is she?
- I don't know for sure yet,

36:26.851 --> 36:28.895
but he's head over heels for her.

36:28.978 --> 36:32.315
I've never seen him
fall for a girl this hard before.

36:36.277 --> 36:37.278
Fine.

36:52.251 --> 36:53.586
What's with the late dinner?

36:54.545 --> 36:55.755
You haven't even finished.

36:56.756 --> 36:58.716
I started eating after some contemplation,

36:58.799 --> 37:00.509
but I don't really have an appetite.

37:00.593 --> 37:02.970
By the way,
the pharmacist has a girlfriend.

37:05.681 --> 37:07.391
He's head over heels for her.

37:11.354 --> 37:12.730
He rarely dates,

37:13.606 --> 37:16.192
but he's fallen hard this time.

37:21.864 --> 37:25.076
Aren't you curious when
he's not the type to fall in love easily?

37:27.078 --> 37:28.996
Why are you so interested in Ji-ho?

37:30.623 --> 37:31.540
Ji-ho?

37:34.543 --> 37:35.753
What else do I call him?

37:36.212 --> 37:39.090
I can't say "that friend" like
you call that guy who's studying.

37:40.591 --> 37:43.427
Also, watch your manners
with other people.

37:43.511 --> 37:44.762
Don't be your silly self.

37:45.972 --> 37:48.224
So I won't be an embarrassment
to your boyfriend?

37:50.977 --> 37:53.229
If that's it, you've really gotten lamer.

37:54.355 --> 37:55.898
I miss my fearless sister.

38:04.615 --> 38:07.535
Si-hoon, I'll be honest with you.

38:08.786 --> 38:10.246
Do you have some time right now?

38:11.539 --> 38:13.165
There's a conference today,

38:13.249 --> 38:15.167
so I only have patients in the afternoon.

38:18.296 --> 38:20.673
Before the bank approves a loan,

38:20.840 --> 38:22.842
it considers one's ability to pay it back.

38:23.968 --> 38:26.762
If you declare less earnings

38:26.846 --> 38:28.180
to pay a lower tax rate,

38:28.264 --> 38:30.474
then the loan you can take out
decreases too.

38:31.225 --> 38:34.020
- Also, you already took out two loans--
- You know,

38:34.103 --> 38:36.105
I should just forget about it.

38:36.188 --> 38:38.274
Someone said that a loan would be easier,

38:38.774 --> 38:40.276
but I should use my own money

38:40.401 --> 38:42.528
even if that means a higher tax rate.

38:42.611 --> 38:43.738
Unbelievable.

38:45.364 --> 38:46.407
I'm sorry about this.

38:47.450 --> 38:49.201
Don't worry about it. It's fine.

38:50.870 --> 38:51.912
It's all good.

38:53.122 --> 38:56.667
Just so you know,
I mentioned your marriage with Jeong-in

38:56.751 --> 38:59.462
to her father over dinner.

39:00.212 --> 39:01.630
You need to step up your game.

39:02.465 --> 39:03.382
What did he say?

39:04.216 --> 39:06.469
You're still not marrying
his beautiful daughter,

39:06.552 --> 39:07.720
so how could he be happy?

39:11.349 --> 39:14.393
Don't be intimidated though.
It'll be all right.

39:14.518 --> 39:16.854
Like I said,
I'm going to help you get the girl.

39:16.937 --> 39:18.397
This is what families are for.

39:18.481 --> 39:21.609
It's why grudges between family members
last long.

39:24.278 --> 39:28.157
I'm not saying that I'm upset
about this loan approval though.

39:28.491 --> 39:29.784
Don't get the wrong idea.

39:34.580 --> 39:36.665
I'll see what I can do about the loan.

39:36.749 --> 39:39.251
See? This is what I was worried about.

39:39.835 --> 39:41.504
You shouldn't...

39:41.921 --> 39:44.256
I'll look into it and get back to you.

39:45.341 --> 39:46.342
Thank you.

39:47.676 --> 39:50.971
Anyway, don't worry too much
about the loan.

39:51.055 --> 39:52.306
Why would I?

39:52.390 --> 39:54.183
It's not like I need it to get by.

39:54.266 --> 39:55.518
Of course not.

39:55.893 --> 39:57.978
When can Jeong-in and I meet you guys?

39:58.062 --> 39:59.480
I already told her we should.

40:00.022 --> 40:01.524
Not this week,

40:01.607 --> 40:04.318
but I'm free any time
next week for dinner.

40:04.693 --> 40:06.237
We can meet anywhere you want too.

40:06.320 --> 40:08.030
Actually, come over to our house.

40:08.114 --> 40:10.658
My wife's a public figure,
so she's comfortable at home.

40:10.741 --> 40:12.034
- Right?
- Sure.

40:12.118 --> 40:14.620
We're good either way, so we'll come over.

40:14.703 --> 40:16.372
- Okay, I'll see you then.
- Sure.

40:16.455 --> 40:17.623
- Bye.
- See you.

40:17.706 --> 40:18.582
Have a good one.

40:31.178 --> 40:33.472
I want to talk to you. Let's meet.

40:38.769 --> 40:39.854
Damn it.

40:41.147 --> 40:42.148
Come in.

40:42.731 --> 40:44.817
Sir, we're calling it a day.

40:44.942 --> 40:46.277
- Sure, good job today.
- Bye.

40:48.821 --> 40:49.864
Hello.

40:51.198 --> 40:53.409
- Would you like some tea?
- No, I'm good.

40:53.742 --> 40:55.244
Instead, and I'm sorry to ask,

40:55.953 --> 40:58.205
but can you buy me digestive medicine?

40:58.289 --> 40:59.331
Sure.

41:00.916 --> 41:02.501
- Hello.
- Hi.

41:13.387 --> 41:14.430
Come in.

41:20.728 --> 41:22.146
I put the house on the market.

41:23.272 --> 41:24.940
What about your loan?

41:26.317 --> 41:27.860
If you can't pay it back soon,

41:28.194 --> 41:29.487
I'll put a rush on the sale.

41:30.696 --> 41:33.073
That won't speed up the divorce, you know.

41:34.408 --> 41:36.285
I'm going to sell it one way or another,

41:37.244 --> 41:38.662
so hand over your legal seal.

41:42.708 --> 41:44.043
Hand it over.

41:44.543 --> 41:46.295
I don't have time to come back for it.

42:00.309 --> 42:02.645
- I won't let you anymore.
- As if you have a choice.

42:02.728 --> 42:04.605
Get back here.

42:05.105 --> 42:07.399
See? What are you going to do?

42:09.109 --> 42:10.528
- Are you all right?
- I...

42:10.986 --> 42:12.154
Why haven't you left?

42:12.988 --> 42:14.073
Thank you.

42:15.074 --> 42:17.409
Tell me when it's ready. I'll see you.

42:18.035 --> 42:19.078
Sure.

42:19.286 --> 42:21.205
I'm leaving too. Let's head out together.

42:22.456 --> 42:23.582
See you tomorrow.

42:25.459 --> 42:27.753
I could help with the paperwork.

42:27.920 --> 42:29.672
I can too as long as there are snacks.

42:29.797 --> 42:31.340
Am I supposed to pay for all that?

42:32.007 --> 42:33.259
You should go home already.

42:33.968 --> 42:36.470
- All right.
- See you tomorrow.

42:43.602 --> 42:45.729
I'm busy tonight.
I'll call you some other time.

42:45.813 --> 42:47.064
Did you two agree to meet?

42:48.524 --> 42:49.441
He's busy today.

42:52.152 --> 42:55.364
The nasty war has begun.

42:57.157 --> 42:58.367
I wish you luck.

43:51.337 --> 43:53.255
PHARMACIST

44:14.318 --> 44:15.861
The person you have reached...

45:11.500 --> 45:12.918
The person you have reached...

46:23.739 --> 46:25.115
Why are you ignoring my calls?

46:26.158 --> 46:27.910
Is that what you're going to do now?

46:29.453 --> 46:31.497
I didn't know you called.
It was on vibrate.

46:32.206 --> 46:35.042
- Did something happen?
- Am I the only one having a hard time?

46:36.877 --> 46:38.253
You're fine?

46:40.339 --> 46:41.673
I guess you're totally fine.

46:44.218 --> 46:45.677
You've got to be kidding me.

46:49.223 --> 46:50.265
Am I a hassle to you?

46:52.643 --> 46:53.644
Am I annoying?

46:54.478 --> 46:55.771
Yes, you are.

46:58.857 --> 47:00.234
You shouldn't have come here.

47:01.819 --> 47:02.820
Why did you come?

47:03.821 --> 47:05.823
We should just go back to being strangers.

47:06.448 --> 47:08.617
What do you expect me to do
if you show up now--

47:42.150 --> 47:43.443
Have you had dinner?

47:49.199 --> 47:50.367
How about we get some?

47:55.831 --> 47:56.915
What are you buying?

47:59.877 --> 48:01.044
Why do I have to buy?

48:01.128 --> 48:02.421
Of course.

48:03.463 --> 48:05.299
I took a taxi to get here.

48:06.425 --> 48:08.260
It's not like I told you to come.

48:10.554 --> 48:11.722
Is that a no?

48:14.099 --> 48:15.309
I'll just go home then.

48:17.269 --> 48:18.687
You're selfish, you know that?

48:28.405 --> 48:29.990
Are you closed?

48:31.158 --> 48:32.200
Oh, it's you.

48:32.576 --> 48:34.036
We already took our last order,

48:34.369 --> 48:36.121
but you're a regular, so come on in.

48:36.705 --> 48:37.873
Please take a seat.

48:38.415 --> 48:39.833
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

48:41.668 --> 48:42.753
Let's sit here.

48:54.723 --> 48:57.726
Everything's good here,
but I especially like the spicy kalguksu.

48:59.061 --> 49:00.687
Then I'll have that.

49:01.855 --> 49:02.856
You should...

49:03.899 --> 49:06.026
order sujebi so that I can have some.

49:07.736 --> 49:08.904
That's what we'll have.

49:09.780 --> 49:10.781
Sure.

49:13.408 --> 49:15.410
One spicy kalguksu and sujebi.

49:15.661 --> 49:17.245
Coming right up.

50:00.372 --> 50:02.249
You said it's good, but I guess it's not.

50:03.667 --> 50:05.335
We could've gone somewhere else.

50:07.754 --> 50:09.631
Actually, I already had dinner.

50:13.510 --> 50:14.928
You must be at ease

50:15.512 --> 50:17.222
since you're not skipping any meals.

50:19.850 --> 50:21.852
Did you want me to lose
my appetite over you?

50:24.604 --> 50:25.856
It's not like you did.

50:33.030 --> 50:34.322
Do you find it a burden

50:36.116 --> 50:37.409
to even text or talk to me?

50:39.202 --> 50:40.495
Greatly.

50:45.792 --> 50:47.836
I shouldn't have gotten involved with you.

50:51.131 --> 50:52.382
Do I seem like a loser?

50:55.761 --> 50:57.012
You're worse.

51:09.858 --> 51:12.110
What time does that coffee shop
we went to close?

51:13.236 --> 51:15.489
Will it still be open
if we go there after dinner?

51:17.574 --> 51:18.700
Aren't you going home?

51:19.534 --> 51:21.620
Will you let me stay at your place
if I don't?

51:23.705 --> 51:25.207
You're really something.

51:52.692 --> 51:53.735
Am I really...

51:57.030 --> 51:58.573
a burden to you?

52:01.409 --> 52:03.328
You came to my house when I needed space,

52:03.411 --> 52:04.746
so of course you're a burden.

52:07.624 --> 52:10.502
If we just let ourselves
follow these feelings,

52:12.754 --> 52:15.340
it'll be much harder for me to stop.

52:15.590 --> 52:16.675
When that happens,

52:17.717 --> 52:19.177
things will be

52:20.720 --> 52:22.389
a lot harder for you.

52:26.560 --> 52:27.602
So up until now,

52:28.895 --> 52:30.689
you've been holding back for me.

52:33.400 --> 52:34.484
That's why

52:35.402 --> 52:37.487
I'm the idiot who couldn't even hug

52:38.238 --> 52:40.657
the woman who cried
after stopping me from talking.

52:45.787 --> 52:48.123
I'm the loser and you're the idiot.

52:56.506 --> 52:58.758
I don't want anyone
to suffer because of me,

53:01.428 --> 53:02.888
so please don't cry from now on.

53:06.516 --> 53:08.143
I didn't cry because of you.

53:10.645 --> 53:12.230
I know you don't like to lose,

53:13.732 --> 53:15.317
but don't be stubborn with me.

53:17.152 --> 53:18.403
It'll only be your loss.

53:23.491 --> 53:24.492
So...

53:27.996 --> 53:29.831
should I stick to doing nothing?

53:30.415 --> 53:31.666
I said I'd be your friend.

53:33.084 --> 53:34.878
Just like how you suggested,

53:35.712 --> 53:36.838
we will...

53:38.965 --> 53:40.342
grab a meal sometimes,

53:40.926 --> 53:42.219
get coffee,

53:43.011 --> 53:44.679
and ask each other how we're doing.

53:47.265 --> 53:48.350
That much we can do.

53:53.980 --> 53:55.690
I don't think I can anymore.

53:56.775 --> 53:58.610
There's nothing I can do about that.

54:02.405 --> 54:03.698
You sound so cold.

54:09.120 --> 54:11.957
Can't you tell that
this is torture for me?

54:18.171 --> 54:19.673
Why should I care?

54:20.840 --> 54:23.677
Again, the mean Lee Jeong-in has surfaced.

54:25.220 --> 54:26.763
You'll be seeing her often now.

54:28.223 --> 54:30.058
I'm known to be a troublemaker.

54:35.939 --> 54:38.566
Help me. I mean it.

54:40.068 --> 54:41.403
I need your help, Jeong-in.

54:43.571 --> 54:45.240
What if I can't?

54:45.782 --> 54:46.950
Then force yourself to.

54:48.910 --> 54:50.453
- No.
- You must.

54:54.833 --> 54:56.042
You're...

54:59.379 --> 55:00.422
too good for me.

56:36.935 --> 56:38.103
What are you doing here?

56:40.730 --> 56:41.898
What brings you by?

56:42.524 --> 56:44.150
I had some business around here.

56:45.693 --> 56:47.112
How come you two are together?

56:48.196 --> 56:50.407
Us? We're friends now.

56:50.824 --> 56:52.158
Oh, well...

56:54.953 --> 56:55.995
What?

56:57.705 --> 56:59.040
The door is closing.

57:05.797 --> 57:07.715
Jeong-in!

57:09.092 --> 57:11.678
Where do you go all the time
when you have nothing to do?

57:11.845 --> 57:13.430
I'm busy despite being broke.

57:13.638 --> 57:15.098
I saw the pharmacist out front.

57:16.474 --> 57:17.434
Really?

57:17.642 --> 57:19.602
He's probably still talking to his friend.

57:20.478 --> 57:22.564
Were you with that guy
that's studying again?

57:22.647 --> 57:24.023
I told you we're friends.

57:24.691 --> 57:26.317
He dropped me off,

57:26.401 --> 57:28.236
but I couldn't invite him in for coffee

57:28.319 --> 57:30.029
because you might be against it.

57:30.697 --> 57:32.991
I'm not that much of a snob, you know.

57:34.492 --> 57:36.578
- Then I'm inviting him in.
- Hey, Jae-in!

57:38.163 --> 57:39.080
Is she insane?

58:14.365 --> 58:16.951
My sister invited you both in.

58:17.452 --> 58:18.661
You should ride shotgun.

58:23.458 --> 58:25.460
Come on. Let's go!

58:59.285 --> 59:00.286
This way.

59:22.183 --> 59:24.352
Come on in. Jeong-in!

59:24.435 --> 59:25.478
Right.

59:27.313 --> 59:29.148
You can wear the slippers.

59:31.609 --> 59:32.819
Come on in.

59:32.902 --> 59:34.404
- Come.
- Okay.

59:37.949 --> 59:39.325
Come on in.

59:39.659 --> 59:40.952
Come on in.

59:41.452 --> 59:42.829
Come this way.

59:45.331 --> 59:47.000
There you go.

59:47.166 --> 59:49.627
Just think that
you're at a friend's house.

59:49.711 --> 59:51.004
Thank you.

59:52.046 --> 59:53.464
So what do we do now?

59:54.924 --> 59:57.552
How should I know? They're your guests.

01:00:03.933 --> 01:00:05.310
I boiled water for the tea.

01:00:05.393 --> 01:00:08.062
So we're having tea? That's boring.

01:00:08.855 --> 01:00:11.274
- Do we have any drinks left?
- I polished them off...

01:00:17.780 --> 01:00:19.198
I should go out and buy some.

01:00:20.158 --> 01:00:21.159
Let's go.

01:00:21.242 --> 01:00:23.995
We'll go and buy the drinks then.

01:00:24.078 --> 01:00:26.623
The convenience store
is quite far away and hard to find.

01:00:26.706 --> 01:00:28.750
- Let's go. We won't be long.
- But...

01:00:30.168 --> 01:00:31.502
Take my credit card then.

01:00:31.586 --> 01:00:33.296
Seo-in gave me some money.

01:01:25.556 --> 01:01:26.557
Hello?

01:01:26.974 --> 01:01:28.434
What did you want to talk about?

01:01:32.271 --> 01:01:33.606
You said you wanted to talk.

01:01:36.734 --> 01:01:39.112
Let's break up.

01:02:21.946 --> 01:02:24.073
It's the same for
my son and your daughter.

01:02:24.198 --> 01:02:26.993
If we aren't careful,
it can end badly for both families.

01:02:27.076 --> 01:02:28.870
Let's not make a rash decision.

01:02:28.953 --> 01:02:31.706
I keep forgetting the old Ji-ho.

01:02:31.789 --> 01:02:33.958
You were fun, smart, and competitive.

01:02:34.041 --> 01:02:36.627
Can I see
that high-spirited version of you again?

01:02:36.711 --> 01:02:39.130
I hear you're with someone,
must seem like the world.

01:02:39.213 --> 01:02:40.131
Not for you anymore?

01:02:40.214 --> 01:02:41.924
It'd be weird if it still was.

01:02:42.008 --> 01:02:43.468
Then you could fall out of love.

01:02:43.551 --> 01:02:45.136
I'd break up
with my girlfriend.

01:02:45.219 --> 01:02:46.304
You'll just let her go?

01:02:46.387 --> 01:02:48.806
I wouldn't get revenge,
but I guess I'd make a scene.

01:02:48.890 --> 01:02:51.142
You must be objective
with those closer to you.

01:02:51.225 --> 01:02:54.103
Blindly believing in them
will drive you off a cliff.

01:02:54.187 --> 01:02:56.230
Could Gi-seok know about the pharmacist?

01:02:56.314 --> 01:02:58.024
Don't think you're safe yet.

01:02:58.107 --> 01:03:00.401
You're the woman he likes?
Do you like him too?

01:03:00.485 --> 01:03:02.236
I like him. Gi-seok has no idea.

01:03:02.320 --> 01:03:03.613
He'll figure it out today.

01:03:03.696 --> 01:03:06.616
I got pissed because
it seemed like she had someone else.

01:03:06.699 --> 01:03:08.618
I want to ask you something just in case.

01:03:11.954 --> 01:03:13.998
Subtitle translation by Liya Choi
